    <section class="info">
        <h1>Rules</h1>
        <p>In this scenario you are a cyber defence professional who is guarding the critical infrastructure of the hospital you work for. Your work will be represented by a central section will have a circle in it. Data packets will emerge at the outside and move towards the centre. Your role is to left click on each packet, bringing up the relevant information and then classify the level of danger it represents.</p>
        <p>When you select the data packet a section will be populated with a run down of information collected from each data packet each of which can provide either positive, neutral or negative responses.</p>
        <h2>Criteria</h2>
        <p>If there are 0 negative attributes then please classify the data packet as safe.</p>
        <p>If there are 1-2 negative attributes then classify the data packet as neutral.</p>
        <p>If there are 3-4 negative attributes then classify the data packet as hostile.</p>
        <h2>Attributes</h2>
        <p>Checksum Value: Valid/Invalid/Zero all are neutral</p>
        <p>Time of receiving data packet: 24 hour clock all are neutral</p>
        <p>IP Address: random IP address all are neutral</p>
        <p>Country: chosen from the made up list all are neutral</p>
        <p>Port Number: 4444 = hostile, 80 = safe</p>
        <p>Protocol: ICMP = hostile, HTTPS = safe</p>
        <p>Fragmentation: Yes= hostile, No = safe</p>
        <p>Certificates: Expired = hostile, Valid = safe</p>
        <button id="proceedToTrial">Start Trial</button>
    </section>

